<subSubSection id="C30565096A59C11A11ECF98442D8FA98" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA036826A59C11D11ECF98442F3F9E4" blockId="3.[151,1437,1408,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B96BEA906A59C11D11ECF9844244F980" bold="true" box="[197,379,1553,1577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D133FF98441B6F980" box="[534,649,1553,1577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="15.100000000000001" valueMax="16.3" valueMin="13.9">13.9–16.3</number>
; head length: 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D120DF9844044F980" box="[804,891,1553,1577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="1.9" valueMax="2.1" valueMin="1.7">1.7–2.1</number>
; head width: 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D1539F9844758F980" box="[1040,1127,1553,1577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="2.65" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.5">2.5–2.8</number>
; pronotal width: 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D140DF98446A7F980" box="[1316,1432,1553,1577]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="15.350000000000001" valueMax="16.8" valueMin="13.9">13.9–16.8</number>
; abdominal width: 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D104BF9A042B8F9E4" box="[354,391,1589,1613]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="7.9">7.9</number>
–10.0.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA036826A59C11D11ECF9CC4040F88C" blockId="3.[151,1437,1408,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Body dorsally dark castaneous with some metallic green shine on pronotum and corium. Ventrally castaneous to dark castaneous and shiny but without iridescent color; abdomen with three longitudinal clear bands. Head in front of eyes reddish to castaneous. Fourth and fifth antennal segments missing. Anterolateral margins of pronotum rugose, with long yellowish stripe on each reaching base of each humeral angle. Metapleuron with distal reddish spot. Metasternal process reddish, branches divergent, curved and evanescent; anterior bifurcation almost completely excavated leaving free part of branches long (
<figureCitation id="13242A076A59C11D13C0F898404DF88C" box="[745,882,1805,1829]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1079]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15, Edessa splendens sp. nov. 10 – 12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14 – 15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D1200F898404DF88C" box="[809,882,1805,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="14.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="14.0">14–15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA036826A59C11D11ECF8A440C6F870" blockId="3.[151,1437,1408,2009]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13242A076A59C11D105CF8A442C0F8E0" box="[373,511,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1079]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15, Edessa splendens sp. nov. 10 – 12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14 – 15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="66">
Figs. 
<number id="3DD724A56A59C11D109CF8A442C0F8E0" box="[437,511,1841,1865]" pageId="3" pageNumber="66" value="11.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="10.0">10–12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Base of posterolateral angles of pygophore slightly tumid. Process of genital cup long, reaching dorsal rim. Ventral rim widely excavated leaving parameres visible in ventral view; lobes large and acuminate close to and below level of posterolateral angle. Paramere large, smooth, with long narrow lobe laterally directed reaching tumid area of posterolateral angle and another large, long, narrow, and rounded projected anteriorly reaching dorsal rim. Segment X with posterior face truncate and uneven.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF60660A6A5EC11A11BEFBD94789FB28" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" targetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BA036826A5EC11A11BEFBD94789FB28" blockId="4.[151,1437,1100,1153]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B96BEA906A5EC11A11BEFBD9426AFBC8" bold="true" box="[151,341,1100,1123]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">FIGURES 10–15,</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D016A5EC11A1075FBD9412FFBCB" box="[348,528,1100,1122]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Edessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96BEA906A5EC11A1075FBD9412FFBCB" box="[348,528,1100,1122]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Edessa splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B96BEA906A5EC11A1331FBD84155FBCB" bold="true" box="[536,618,1101,1122]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25857EB6A5EC11A1331FBD84155FBCB" box="[536,618,1101,1122]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
10–12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14–15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA036826A5EC11A11ECFB3842D8FA98" blockId="4.[151,1436,1197,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13242A076A5EC11A10BDFB3842D4FB6C" box="[404,491,1197,1221]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 15" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1100,1123]" captionTargetBox="[166,1414,217,1071]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1079]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 15, Edessa splendens sp. nov. 10 – 12, male, pygophore; 10, dorsal view; 11, posterior view; 12, ventral view. 13, Female, genital plates. 14 – 15, Metasternal process; 15, lateral view; 16, ventral view. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205149/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
Fig. 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A10E5FB3842D4FB6C" box="[460,491,1197,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A13A6FB3841A2FB6C" box="[655,669,1197,1221]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
convex, slightly compressed near lateral margin, acuminate, long, almost reaching level of the gonocoxite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A1348FB44414EFB40" box="[609,625,1233,1257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="9.0">9</number>
; inner margin slanting, imbricate at base and widely excavated distally leaving gonocoxite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A105DFB6042BDFAA4" box="[372,386,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="9.0">9</number>
entirely visible. Laterotergite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A13FFFB6041DBFAA4" box="[726,740,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
uniformly castaneous. Laterotergite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A15A8FB6047B0FAA4" box="[1153,1167,1269,1293]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="9.0">9</number>
oblong; base excavated close to apex of gonocoxite 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A10FBFA8C42DDFA98" box="[466,482,1305,1329]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30565096A5EC11A11ECFAA84723FAD0" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA036826A5EC11A11ECFAA84723FAD0" blockId="4.[151,1436,1197,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B96BEA906A5EC11A11ECFAA84272FAFF" bold="true" box="[197,333,1341,1366]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is recognizable by the lack of iridescent color on the head, scutellum, and ventral surface. The shape of gonocoxites 
<number id="3DD724A56A5EC11A10D0FAF44136FAD0" box="[505,521,1377,1401]" pageId="4" pageNumber="67" value="8.0">8</number>
, pygophore, and parameres are also diagnostic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
